Introduction

Jay Chang is an American singer and lyricist currently signed under FM Entertainment. Known for his versatility and engaging stage presence, he has made a mark in the K-pop industry as a member of the boy group ONE PACT and the project group B.D.U. Additionally, he is a pre-debut member of M.O.N.T Arena. Jay gained widespread recognition through his participation in several reality survival shows, including Under Nineteen, Boys Planet, and Build Up: Vocal Boy Group Survivor. He made his official solo debut on October 17, 2023, with his mini album Late Night, showcasing his vocal and lyrical talents.

Jay‚Äôs journey began in 2018 when he appeared on Under Nineteen as part of the vocal team. Although he was eliminated in the early rounds, this experience paved the way for his future in the industry. In 2022, he was introduced as a pre-debut member of M.O.N.T Arena, demonstrating his potential as a rising star. In 2023, Jay competed on Boys Planet, where he ranked 10th overall, narrowly missing a spot in ZEROBASEONE. Later that year, he officially debuted as a solo artist with Late Night and joined ONE PACT, debuting with the group‚Äôs mini album Moment on November 30.

In 2024, Jay participated in Mnet‚Äôs Build Up: Vocal Boy Group Survivor and secured his debut in the project group B.D.U, releasing their mini album Wishpool on June 26. His musical journey continued with the release of his second solo mini album, Neighborhood, on November 22. With a career marked by persistence and diverse talents, Jay Chang continues to captivate audiences worldwide.
